      "subtasks": [],
      "created": "2019-10-28T09:27:27.909+0000",
      "description": "Currently, the Capacity Scheduler queue configuration supports two ways to set queue capacity.\r\n * In percentage of all available resources as a float ( eg. 25.0 ) means 25% of the resources of its parent queue for all resource types equally (eg. 25% of all memory, 25% of all CPU cores, and 25% of all available GPU in the cluster) The percentages of all queues has to add up to 100%.\r\n * In an absolute amount of resources ( e.g. memory=4GB,vcores=20,yarn.io/gpu=4 ). The amount of all resources in the queues has to be less than or equal to all resources in the cluster.{color:#de350b}Actually, the above is not supported, we only support memory and vcores now in absolute mode, we should extend in\u00a0{color} YARN-10503.\r\n\r\nApart from these two already existing ways, there is a demand to add capacity percentage of each available resource type separately. (eg. {{memory=20%,vcores=40%,yarn.io/gpu=100%}}).\r\n At the same time, a similar concept should be included with queues maximum-capacity as well.",
      "priority": {
        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/priority/3",
        "iconUrl": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/major.svg",
        "name": "Major",
        "id": "3"
      },
